<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="EnableIptables" version="5.0">
 <title xml:id="SysMgmtServices">Enable Iptables</title>
 <para>
  The iptables daemon is responsible for providing host-based firewall
  capability for IPv4 and ICMP. This module will check for the iptables
  package and turn the service on (if not already on). Refer to the
  <filename>iptables</filename> man pages for information on how to
  configure the firewall.
 </para>
 <para>
  <note>
   <para>
    The SUSE and openSUSE operating system wrap iptables in a different
    startup mechanism. Please refer to the operating system
    documentation for further assistance.
   </para>
  </note>
 </para>
